cards.front: What are Newton's laws of motion?
cards.back: First law: An object at rest stays at rest and an object in motion stays in motion with the same speed and direction unless acted upon by an unbalanced force. Second law: The acceleration of an object is directly proportional to the net force acting on it and inversely proportional to its mass. Third law: For every action, there is an equal and opposite reaction.
